what if the type is unknown but the symbols are matched by the frontend? I fear it's going to return "!unknown!" here.
Instead of:
return Optional.of(typeCastTree.type().symbolType().name());
I would use something like so we use directly the TypeTree, which, even unresolved, will display the correct name:
return Optional.of(ExpressionsHelper.concatenate(typeCastTree.type()));

